<span id="freeTextContainer5782429848811891604">4.5 for this novel centered around 4 siblings in New York. It’s 1969, these Jewish siblings ages 13-7, two boys and two girls, hear on the street that there is a woman in the city who can tell fortunes. They visit her and she sees them one at a time, and tells them the date they will die.<br/>So we follow these kids through the years and see how this information changes the way they live and their relationships with their family and others.<br/>I really enjoyed this book!</span>

          </span>
